{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"edec76e9-03d7-4857-ac53-6025394650c3","content":"This is a TUnit project (v0.6.120) which uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** natively. TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` instead of VSTest's `--filter`.\n\nTo run only `SmsNotificationTests`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\n**Why `dotnet run` instead of `dotnet test`?** TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (the project has `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`). The MTP filter syntax for TUnit is `--treenode-filter` with a path pattern: `/<assembly>/<namespace>/<class>/<test>`. The `*` wildcards match any segment.\n\nIf you prefer `dotnet test`, you can also use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nBoth will run only the two `SmsNotificationTests` tests (`SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ce156716-6fde-4a34-887d-43430e4de53b","outputTokens":265,"requestId":"D007:12531F:1527BC6:188D168:69EC1707"},"id":"6008e125-8540-47b2-918a-579ba04be1b7","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:21:17.682Z","parentId":"2047c19d-c7d2-40d6-a781-b93ead51e176"}
